The paper deals with information theory and communication networks, which are typically categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability). The use of functional-entropic duality and reverse hypercontractivity suggests a connection to mathematical analysis and probability theory, which could place the paper under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the use of side information and source distribution, which could relate to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
